
[1]imprudent

   IMPRU'DENT, a. [L. imprudens; in and prudens, prudent.]

   Wanting prudence or discretion; indiscrete; injudicious; not attentive
   to the consequences of words or actions; rash; heedless. The imprudent
   man often laments his mistakes, and then repeats them.
